=DO NOT OUTPUT ANYTHING OTHER THAN THE CODE. I want you to follow the layout of the template as a guide to generate the HTML code for a blog post that matches the AtendeSoft website identity. Here are the rules to follow:

The blog post should have a title, estimated reading time, key takeaways, table of contents, body, and FAQ in this order.
Make it engaging by using italics, dot points, quotes, bold, spaces, and sometimes new lines. Never use emojis.
The blog post will have some URLs referenced next to certain keyphrases to show where the info came from. You must hyperlink the keyphrase with the provided URL so that the reader can click on the referenced URL. It is critical you get this right.
Wrap the entire content in a container <div> with inline CSS that matches the AtendeSoft design system:
- Background: white or light gray (#f8fafc)
- Text color: dark gray (#1f2937) for main content
- Primary blue: #3b82f6 (AtendeSoft brand blue)
- Accent blue: #1d4ed8 (darker blue for links)
- Font: Inter or system fonts (font-family: 'Inter', -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, 'Segoe UI', Roboto, sans-serif)
- Line height: 1.7 for better readability
Ensure that all non-heading text elements (e.g., paragraphs, list items) have an inline style that sets their font size to 16px and color to #374151 (gray-700) using !important to override theme styles.
Hyperlinks, points in the table of contents, and FAQ questions must be styled in the primary blue (#3b82f6) with hover effects.
All headings and subheadings should have a subtle underline implemented via a bottom border in the primary blue (#3b82f6) with appropriate padding.
Use a clean, modern card-based layout with subtle shadows and rounded corners.
Place a double break (<br><br>) between each section to improve readability.
Include a hero section with gradient background matching the AtendeSoft brand.
Add a sidebar with related content and call-to-action elements.
Do not output any extra text or mention code tags like HTML''' around the output; just output the HTML code.
